@@TJvInstallerPage.Installer
Description:
This is the installer used for the installation (this property MUST BE FILLED). The component extract program name and the picture from the installer. When putting the component on the form, it automatically completes this property by the first installer found on your form, but you should always check he has found the correct installer

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.NextPage
Description:
This is the page showed after this one. When the user clicks the next button and if a page is specified, the event OnNextPage is fired, then the page is shown and the event OnNextPageShown is fired. You can abort the step with the event OnNextPage. If not page is specified, the event OnNext is fired instead.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnHide
Description:
This event occurs when the dialog has been hidden.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnNext
Description:
This event occurs when the user clicks the next button and when no page has been specified in the NextPage property.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnNextPage
Description:
This event occurs when the user has clicked the next button and when the next page is going to be showed. Use this event to prevent the page to be shown.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnNextPageShown
Description:
This event occurs when the user has clicked the next button and the previous page has been shown. The next page is specified in the NextPage property

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnPrevious
Description:
This event occurs when the user clicks the previous button and when no page has been specified in the PreviousPage property.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnPreviousPage
Description:
This event occurs when the user has clicked the previous button and when the previous page is going to be showed. Use this event to prevent the page to be shown.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnPreviousPageShown
Description:
This event occurs when the user has clicked the previous button and the previous page has been shown. The previous page is specified in the PreviousPage property

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.OnShow
Description:
This event occurs when the dialog has been shown.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvInstallerPage.PreviousPage
Description:
This is the page showed before this one. When the user clicks the previous button and if a page is specified, the event OnPreviousPage is fired, then the page is shown and the event OnPreviousPageShown is fired. You can abort the step with the event OnPreviousPage. If not page is specified, the event OnPrevious is fired instead.

